Adding Trend and Season to Find the Lowest-Forecast-RMSE Model

In my previous post, I experimented with various model structures on various lags. All of the previous models include a constant and trend. Since Employment, Inflation, IPI exit trend, and theoritically all 4 variables could have seasonal properities. In this post, I plan to add both trend and season=12 in the models. The RMSEs show a great improvement.
Although 3 of the series are seasonally adjusted, the outputs show adding season generally lowers the forecast RMSE.

3. Analyze the Forecast Error of the Best Model

Employment forecast error doesn’t pass the ADF test or the Ljung-Box test up to 24 lags. The correlogram suggests an AR(1) effect.

Inflation forecast error doesn’t pass the ADF test or the Ljung-Box test up to 24 lags. The correlogram suggests an AR(2) effect.

Next, I can experiment with variance decomposition and inpulse reponses for the models.
